{ Taking control over d4 } 15. a4 Rb8 16. Nf5 Bf8
{ Not letting White trade the bishop. It's not that this bishop is super-strong right now, instead Black rather hopes to use his space advantage. As we know, the rule if we have space advantage is not to trade pieces ! }
17. axb5 axb5 18. Qg4 Kh8
{ White's play on the kingside shouldn't reach anywhere, as Black has many more defenders. }
19. Qh4 Nd4 { Attacking c2 and trading the White's f5-knight. } 20. Ne3
{ Please, stop for a second and find a winning tactical idea for Black ! }
20... Nxc2 21. Nxc2 Qxd3
{ Black gets two pawns for a piece and attacks two pieces. However, you had to see more than this, as White has a defensive idea now ! }
22. Qh5
{ The only challenging move, even though it still loses. White attacks the rook and goes Qd1 next. If you hadn't seen this, stop and think ! }
22... Be6 23. Qd1 Red8 24. Nf3 Qxe4
{ Black didn't get a piece back, but he already won three pawns and will take the fourth one on b3 right now. Also, white's pieces - let's say, the c2-knight and the b2-bishop are very passive. There is no salvation for White. }
